## Updating the template

Our investor update has gone through several iterations over the years. In the
early days, we included sections on hiring, feedback, and upcoming features.
After reading blog posts by
[Elad Gil](http://blog.eladgil.com/2015/05/investor-update-emails.html) and
[Aaron K. Harris](http://www.aaronkharris.com/investor-updates), Sid developed
our current version with their insights in mind and narrowed the scope of our
update to the following sections: thanks, asks, key metrics, lowlights,
highlights, and next month expectations.

When I joined GitLab, the investor update looked cluttered, and from a reader‚Äôs
perspective, I had difficulty absorbing the information. Below is an example of
an old update with the former template. Please note that some names have been
